{
  "_notes": [
    "Reference template for universal_civ5_pipeline_spartan_artfix_v9.py using the renamed Mississippian PNG pack.",
    "Extract MississippianNewArt_Renamed.zip into C:/Repos/PNGtoDDSConverter/Input/Mississippian/ so the PNG paths below resolve.",
    "mod_data_dir is intentionally omitted so check/build can run before the mod folder exists. Use --mod-data-dir in PowerShell when importing into an installed mod.",
    "PowerShell check: py -3 .\\universal_civ5_pipeline_spartan_artfix_v9.py --config .\\Mississippian_art_reference_v1.json --check-only",
    "PowerShell build: py -3 .\\universal_civ5_pipeline_spartan_artfix_v9.py --config .\\Mississippian_art_reference_v1.json",
    "Normal and alpha icons use the Spartan League v8 footprint: 0.65625 of each cell, so 256px cells get about 168px visible art.",
    "Unit flags are kept on the separate Civ V unit-flag profile, not the normal circular-icon footprint.",
    "Normal atlas index map: 0 civ, 1 leader, 2 ChunkeyWarrior, 3 RiverRaider, 4 PlatformMound, 5 CahokiaPlaza, 6 PalisadeVillage, 7 MoundsOfTheSun, 8 RiverTrade, 9 MaizeFloodplain, 10 SacredCopper.",
    "Black-background glyph sources retain their _black filename suffix and are processed through black-to-transparent glyph profiles.",
    "This art pack does not include a Map_Mississippian512.png source, so map_image and map_output_name are intentionally omitted.",
    "GreatSun_Scene.png is included as the leader scene source. DawnOfMan_Mississippian.png is the Dawn of Man source."
  ],
